& [OpeningPosition] is the public boundary
  + [claim] is this project did not produce a proof of any unsolved Millennium Prize problem
  + [value] is the work clarified what kind of theorem or construction would be needed for progress
  + [method] is source ideas were translated into formal proof obligations, then blocked where construction, transfer, propagation, completeness, or reconstruction was missing

& [ProblemSummaries] is the six-lane summary
  + [bsd] is Birch and Swinnerton-Dyer
    = missing_shape: a mechanism producing enough independent sources for the analytic rank, measured in the same frame, with upper-control closure
    = plain_reading: special points or cycles can be meaningful, but point existence alone does not prove the rank equality
  + [navier_stokes] is Navier-Stokes Existence and Smoothness
    = missing_shape: a deterministic one-sided pressure-Hessian or pressure-strain inequality at continuation scale
    = plain_reading: geometric depletion and alignment are useful only if they become a propagated estimate strong enough to prevent blowup
  + [hodge] is Hodge Conjecture
    = missing_shape: a construction that turns arbitrary rational Hodge classes into algebraic cycles, or correspondences that do so
    = plain_reading: special families and normal functions organize the problem, but the Clay target needs actual algebraic cycle output
  + [p_vs_np] is P versus NP
    = missing_shape: polynomial refutation or simulation power for hard SAT or 3-SAT instances, or a barrier-aware lower-bound route
    = plain_reading: local consistency and tractable CSP fragments are meaningful but do not settle NP-complete completeness
  + [yang_mills] is Yang-Mills Existence and Mass Gap
    = missing_shape: continuum Schwinger functions or Euclidean measure satisfying OS properties, reconstruction, observables, and decay-to-gap transfer
    = plain_reading: lattice models and confinement intuition are not enough without a reconstructed continuum theory
  + [poincare] is Poincare Conjecture
    = missing_shape: none in this project
    = plain_reading: Poincare is already solved externally; Symbolic Ricci Flow here is only a research-organization model

& [CrossProblemLesson] is the shared result
  + [lesson_001] is meaningful metaphors must be separated from proof obligations
  + [lesson_002] is scoped successes teach shape but do not automatically transfer
  + [lesson_003] is the recurring missing objects are construction, transfer, propagation, completeness, and reconstruction
  + [lesson_004] is audit targets should be checked stage by stage before any authority is admitted

& [NextUse] is how this artifact should be used
  + [use] is orientation, communication, and target selection
  + [not_use] is proof, publication as a solution, or authority replacement for formal mathematics
  + [next_step] is choose one concrete audit target or implement the Symbolic Ricci Flow scoring prototype

